node.text: Well…I got this nursery done just in time to move🙈😂 So many of y’all are asking for updates on our current moving status, so I thought I would tell you what’s happening as of right now…with a warning that it could change at any moment 😜 So we definitely sold our house and will be closing on the sale on July 30th! We were supposed to be buying our new property on the same day, but an issue with the appraisal came up, and once again we are back to holding out collective breath while we wait for answers and (prayerfully) a new closing date in August😬 We are thankful to be able to “rent back” and stay in our current house through August, which will give us time to close, get fences up at the new property, move the animals and get our household goods packed up and into storage. The current plan is to rent some RVs for a month while we build out several cabins that will be our temporary homes while we build our final home. We will also be building our new barn at the same time! It’s a LOT to process, but we have come up with several “out-of-the-box” ideas to make this all work😰 Ultimately, we aren’t worried or afraid of what might happen…God has been so good and faithful throughout this process, and we aren’t about to quit trusting him now! Sharing more in stories so don’t miss the deets😜❤️

When we faithfully walk through tough circumstances, knowing that God is in control and has a plan, we will still face the enemy’s arrows. In fact, satan often works overtime during those trials. It takes constant reminders of God’s sovereignty and ability to overcome ANY struggles we may face…in HIS time.  Our journey to adopt Ben was just one of the many faith walks we have had to be willing to take with our kids. It’s hard when you want something so so much, but you feel like God isn’t going to do it for you, so you try to step in…spoiler alert…it never works😬 And that’s satan whispering in your ear by the way! You have to denounce him, tell him he has NO AUTHORITY over your situation, and repeatedly turn your trust back over to God. Y’all, I have literally had to do this multiple times each day, especially when the battle is raging and Satan is digging in his heels to win you over! Reminder: 
GOD ALWAYS WINS!!!

node.text: Ever have “one of those days” y’all?! I had to grab this photo from Emily @pumpkinvinecreekfarm (she always gets the BEST farm photos on our farm!)! And after the day we had today, it seemed very fitting for a post! As I type, we are heading down to Amelia Island for my hubby’s annual Georgia Dental Convention. We are thankful to be able to attend every year, but almost didn’t make it today due to a hold-up with our travel papers for our foster babes😰 Thankfully, all went through, and we are now on our way…about 5 hours late and thoroughly exhausted…but on our way nonetheless. Unfortunately, we may have breathed a sigh of relief a bit too early, as we ended up getting more bad news about the appraisal on the land we are buying (flashbacks to the  Bremen property y’all)… and just like that, we are back in the muck of not knowing if we will have property by the time we need to move in August 🥴 Earlier today, as I felt a wave of panic catch me off guard, I was able to remember “but God!” Sovereign. Able. Good. I walked into the kitchen, turned on my praise music, and danced with my babies. And now, as I wonder where we will end up, I can still have peace, knowing that God has this. He is in control. His ways may be unknown to us, but they are good🙌🏻 Ending “one of those days” with a peace that passes understanding🙌🏻 He’s a good, good father.❤️

node.text:
A new normal…

Discovering what it means to be a “NICU parent.” Long days, even longer nights…small wins & big setbacks. 

Although I’ve given birth 8 times and have had 2 other NAS (Neonatal Abstinence Syndrome) babies from foster care, I’ve never had the blessing of being present during these long hours. It was always one of the hardest parts of our journey with Ben…knowing that we weren’t there for those 3 weeks…knowing that he was alone, knowing that we missed out on that critical bonding period💔

These last 6 days in the hospital have been so precious for me. But they’ve also given me a much more clear reality of what NAS babies experience. It has given me insight into Ben’s world that I never understood. It has given me a more clear vision of the damage that occurs in these babies, and the lifetime ramifications. I not only have a new perspective, but I also have a new desire to see more education and some laws set up to benefit these tiny souls.

Today I am thankful that we have a God who can heal🙌🏻 A God who can protect 🙌🏻 A God who loves us so so much🙌🏻 

And no matter what the future seems to hold, we know that God is able to move the mountains we may see ahead🙌🏻 We’ve witnessed it with Ben…so so many times, and we put our faith in Him to do it again🙌🏻

node.text: He gives...& he takes away. That’s a hard truth. And the taking can rock us to our core. We can choose to live in the pain, the hurt, the frustration, the insecurity and the disappointment, or we can rejoice in truth, knowing that he is STILL a good, good father, and that HIS plan is still in the works🙌🏻 Walking away from this property that we were certain was meant for us, but confident that God not only has us tightly in his grip, but has gone before and made a way for something even better 🙌🏻 Rejoicing in his wisdom and grace today🙌🏻❤️
